PAPER TOC SIDEBAR FIX (2026-05-29): user reported the paper sidebar pushes content DOWN. ROOT CAUSE: docs/paper.html body is display:flex flex-direction:column (head style line 16); children topbar/title-block/abstract-block/.toc/article stack vertically, so the .toc Contents block (was lines 126-178) sat BETWEEN abstract and article and pushed the article down instead of beside it. FIX (standalone docs/paper.html only): wrapped <div class=toc> + <article> in <div class=paper-body>, added .paper-body{display:grid;grid-template-columns:var(--sidebar-width) minmax(0,1fr);gap:32px;align-items:start;max-width:min(110ch,94vw);margin:24px auto;padding:0 32px} (the anentrypoint-design kit grid idiom from app-shell.css:282, using the kit token --sidebar-width=220px). .paper-body > .toc becomes position:sticky top:72px max-height:calc(100vh-88px) overflow-y:auto; .paper-body > article max-width:none. @media(max-width:900px) collapses to single-column stacked (toc static). BROWSER-WITNESSED live (served docs/ :3091): desktop 1036px -> display:grid gridCols "220px 657.838px", tocTop==artTop, tocRight<=artLeft -> sideBySide:true stackedBug:false; mobile 390px -> single col, stacked:true, toc static. KEY FINDING: the DEPLOYED /paper/ route (site/theme.mjs) was ALREADY correct - theme.mjs:262 hoists .toc to a direct child of #ds-article-host + adds .has-toc, :350-409 #ds-article-host.has-toc is a two-column sticky-rail grid with mobile-stack@900px. The bug was STANDALONE docs/paper.html only. extractArticle (theme.mjs:19) strips the source <head> <style> (comment at :485) so the standalone paper must self-contain its grid CSS in head; the /paper route restyles via its own injected block. My .paper-body wrapper is handled gracefully on /paper/ (theme.mjs hoists .toc out of it; the article-containing div becomes the :not(.toc) grid-column:2 cell). Sibling docs (crates/skills/distribution/made-with/stats) have NO .toc (grep=0) so scope is paper-only. Both surfaces now behaviorally consistent two-column sticky-rail grids.